    oc:directiveContent "Include 'think step by step' in prompts to improve counting accuracy. Define rules for edge cases: partial appearances, people entering/exiting frame, and mode changes (e.g., walking to cycling)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Chain-of-thought reasoning improves the model's ability to track and differentiate objects across video frames." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_70235f03 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When crafting counting prompts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use vague prompts like 'count everything in this video'. Always specify explicit inclusion/exclusion criteria (e.g., 'ONLY count people walking on foot, DO NOT count cyclists')." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Vague prompts lead to ambiguous and inconsistent counts; explicit rules reduce misclassification of similar object types." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_77b57c07 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When prompting Gemini for object counts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always request structured output using <answer>N</answer> XML-like tags in prompts for reliable numeric parsing. Include fallback regex extraction for any number in the response." ;
    oc:hasRationale "LLM responses are variable; structured tags provide a deterministic anchor point for parsing, and fallback extraction prevents total failure." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_83c0c4b6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When uploading and processing videos" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Implement upload_and_wait with a max timeout (default 300s) and polling interval (5s). On FAILED state, raise error. On timeout, fail gracefully. For batch processing, add retry logic with exponential backoff for rate limits." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Gemini video processing can hang; timeouts prevent indefinite blocking, and exponential backoff handles transient rate limit errors." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a7bc1a1a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When uploading videos to Gemini API" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use File API upload for videos >20MB; use inline bytes only for small files. Always wait for processing to complete before sending analysis requests." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Surveillance footage is typically large and the File API handles streaming and processing; inline bytes may fail or timeout for large files." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e7885d25 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before executing any video counting task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify GEMINI_API_KEY is set, video file exists and is in a supported format (MP4, MPEG, MOV, AVI, FLV, MPG, WebM, WMV, 3GPP), and network connectivity is available before starting analysis." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Prevents wasted time on uploads that will fail due to missing prerequisites." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ff333633 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When interpreting counting results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Counting accuracy degrades with crowded scenes, occlusion (objects blocking each other), low resolution, distant objects, and poor camera angles. The model may misclassify similar objects (e.g., motorcyclist as cyclist)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are inherent limitations of the Gemini video understanding model that cannot be fully mitigated by prompting alone." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

